      <div class="SOTTO_PARA"><a name="DUC48538e48257c10058cb8f04d994144d2"></a>Disassembly of the clutch cover
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e14886"> </a>Remove the plug (1) from the cover with the relevant O-ring (2), and the plug (3) with the relevant washer (4).
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_9_031102044.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e14891"> </a>Undo the fixing screw (5) of the inner cover (6).
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e14893"> </a>Remove the inner cover (6) and the sounddeadening panel (7).
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e14895"> </a>Remove the circlip (8) and withdraw the shim (9) and the sealing ring (10).
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e14897"> </a>The drilled bush (11) is mounted to the cover by a forced interference fit. Remove it using a suitable puller.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e14899"> </a>Visually inspect the sealing ring (10) and replace it if necessary.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_9_031202045.jpg"></center>
      </div>
